USING CLOUD 9 OR C9 IDE DASHBOARD
To run a rails application:
https://docs.c9.io/running_a_rails_app.html
1-Open the terminal and type gem install rails
When done, type rails new example -d mysql
2-Edit your database configuration in configs/database.yml
3-Type rails s -b $IP -p $PORT
Note :- after point 3, we do not need to use rails server command to start.
